args:
The party finally leaves Grams, only to fall into
a Templar ambush. Suddenly, Volk also bursts
onto the scene, forcing the party to leave the
Templars to the Watch, and face off with him.
Yeah, except it's super dark\nand I can't see a darn thing!
Your Highness! There's light up ahead!
I think we've finally found\nyour path out of Grams.
Aw yeah, we made it out!\nSo long, Grams! See ya in... Huh?
At last, we have found the seventh scion\nof Alberia and his retinue.
So they DID know who we were...
It certainly took you long enough\nto see through our disguise.
Those shameless fabrications you fed\nus earlier about being merchants? Pah!
Her Holiness Pope Origa and His Eminence\nCardinal Graht have ordered you to be\ndelivered to the Curia with all speed.
I'm afraid we must courteously decline.\nWe've not the time to spare.
Please tell them we will take them up on\ntheir generous offer some other time.

Then you choose the way of pain.
If you do not come with us willingly,
we will see you stuffed into sacks
and dragged there like chattel.
What's wrong with you dogs?! Fight!
Stealing is an act of treachery, you know?
I'M the one who will make the fake prince\nand the filthy spawn of Zacharias pay!\nThey will feel the bite of MY fangs!
Dammit, I KNEW it was Volk!
Oh, I know him. I know him very well.
I've no idea who this new knave is,\nso we'll just sort the lot of you together!
This is a most worrisome situation.\nFighting Volk or the Templars would be\nbad enough, but both at once?
Are my eyes going, or is that...?
It's the Watch and the trainees!
I thought I told you not to get involved!
Sorry, Captain, but there's nothing\nwe wouldn't do for you.
And now it's our turn to fight for you!
I can't thank you people enough...\nBut in that case, so be it!
The Watch and I will deal with the\nTemplars, {player_name}!
The rest of you can sort out...that one.
You heard the man, Volk!\nCome at us, if you dare!

Naught ever changes. The strong are a 
sickness... Those who have are a
sickness... And the only choice is to purge
them all!

We are Agito! Fangs of the fangless!
You people are fat and sick with privilege,
and thus do I offer up your lives to the
oppressed people of this city!
